**Migration map:** For a full list of components to migrate with complexity and target layout, see [widget-migration-map.md](../../widget-migration-map.md).

## Context and constraints

- The package is **complicated and a mess**; reorganization must be done carefully.
- **Some components have multiple versions** (e.g. TS_Input / TS_V2_Input, TS_Checkbox / TS_CheckboxV2, TS_CollapsableContainer / TS_CollapsableContainerV2, TS_TextArea / TS_V2_TextArea).
- **Dependent packages** (e.g. editable-item, other app-level packages) already import from this package. They are currently broken but we must **keep export names and types consistent** so that once the package is reorganized, consumers can keep using the same imports (e.g. `TS_InputV2`, `BaseAppLevelProps_TS_InputV2`, `TemplatingProps_TS_InputV2` from `@nu-art/thunder-widgets`).
- **Only the TS_Input family** (and other components that have versions) get their own **concept folder** with v1 / v2 / vN subfolders. Other components stay in their current locations or get a single concept folder as needed.

---

## Target structure (concept-based + version folders)

### Per-component layout

For each **component that has versions** (e.g. Input, TextArea, Checkbox, CollapsableContainer):

- **One top-level concept folder** under `src/main/<concept>/`, e.g. `input`, `textarea`, `checkbox`, `collapsable-container`.
- Under that concept:
  - **v1/** — current “v1” implementation (e.g. class-based `TS_Input`).
  - **v2/** — current “v2” implementation (e.g. `TS_InputV2` from current `TS_V2_Input`).
  - **v3/** — **new**: recreate the component as a **function component** (same API surface where possible).

**Example (Input):**

- Current: `components/TS_Input/`, `components/TS_V2_Input/` (and partial `input/v1/`, `input/v2.ts`).
- Target:
  - `src/main/input/v1/` — TS_Input (and TS_BaseInput, TS_TextArea if they belong to the same family).
  - `src/main/input/v2/` — TS_InputV2 (and any v2-specific types).
  - `src/main/input/v3/` — new function component for Input with same public contract.

Components that **do not** have multiple versions today get a single folder (e.g. one folder per component); only versioned components get v1 / v2 / v3 subfolders.

---

## Package exports (versioned entry points)

- **Export shape:** Expose versioned subpaths so consumers can opt into a major line: e.g. `v1`, `v2`, `vN`.
- **Semantics per version:**
  - **vN** exposes the **N** implementation of each component.
  - If a component **does not exist** in version N, that entry point **re-exports the previous version** for that component so the same export names exist and dependent code does not break.
- **Default/main entry:** The main package entry (e.g. `"."`) can re-export a chosen default (e.g. “latest” or v2 where available, v1 fallback) so existing `import { TS_InputV2 } from '@nu-art/thunder-widgets'` keeps working with **identical export names and types**.

**Critical:** Public type names (e.g. `TS_InputV2`, `BaseAppLevelProps_TS_InputV2`, `TemplatingProps_TS_InputV2`) must remain available from the main entry and/or the versioned entries so editable-item and other app-level packages do not need import path changes for types and components they already use.

---

## Playwright tests (one suite per component, all versions)

- For **each component we move**, add **Playwright tests** in the **same move** (do not defer tests to a later step).
- **Prefer a single test suite** (same scenarios) run against **all versions** (v1, v2, v3) so we can assert that **behavior is consistent across versions**.
- Tests should be in this package (e.g. under `src/test/` or the project’s playwright layout) and run via BAI for this package.

---

## Execution order (when we do move)

**One component per move.** A single move = exactly one component (e.g. Input only, or TextArea only). Never move or consolidate two different components in the same step (e.g. do not do Input and TextArea together). One concept, one move; then the next concept in a separate move.

**Every move is complete.** For that single component, in one step do all of the following. Do not do "consolidation only" or "layout only" — each move includes v3 and tests.

1. **One component at a time** (e.g. Input first, then TextArea, then Checkbox, etc.).
2. For **that one component only**:
   - Create target folders: `<concept>/v1/`, `<concept>/v2/`, `<concept>/v3/`.
   - Move/copy v1 and v2 implementations into v1/ and v2/.
   - **Implement v3** as a function component (same API surface where possible).
   - Wire exports so the main entry and versioned entries (v1, v2, vN) expose the correct names and fallbacks.
   - **Add Playwright tests** for that component; same suite runs against v1, v2, and v3.
3. **Keep export types consistent** — no renaming of public component or type names; only file/folder layout and re-exports change.
4. After each component, verify dependent packages (editable-item, etc.) still resolve and type-check with the same import paths.

**A move is completed only when the tests are passing.** Do not consider the move done until the Playwright suite for that component runs (v1, v2, v3) and all tests pass. If tests fail, fix the implementation or tests until they pass before moving on to the next component.

---

## Summary

| Item | Rule |
|------|------|
| **One component per move** | A single move = exactly one component (one concept). Never move two components (e.g. Input and TextArea) in the same step. |
| **Every move is complete** | Each move includes: consolidate v1/v2 into concept folders, **create v3 (function component)**, **and add Playwright tests** (same suite for v1, v2, v3). No consolidation-only or layout-only steps. |
| **Layout** | One concept folder per component family (e.g. `input/`). Under it: `v1/`, `v2/`, `v3/` (v3 = new function component). Only versioned components get v1/v2/v3. |
| **Exports** | Versioned entry points (v1, v2, vN). Each vN exposes N implementation; missing components in vN fall back to previous version. Main entry keeps same export names for backward compatibility. |
| **Types** | Keep export type names unchanged so dependents (editable-item, app packages) do not need import changes. |
| **Tests** | One Playwright test suite per moved component; same tests run on v1, v2, v3 for consistency. Required in the same move as the component. |
| **Move complete when** | The move is **completed only when the tests are passing**. Do not consider the move done until the component’s Playwright suite runs and all tests pass. |
| **Moves** | Do not move anything until this plan is agreed; then execute one component at a time, with v3 and tests in every move. |
